acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

escrowMessage(bytes32,bytes,bytes,(uint4.details: Called by other contracts. Any integrating application should check:     1. That incentive.maxGasAck is sufficient! Otherwise, an off-chain agent needs to re-submit the ack.     2. That incentive.maxGasDelivery is sufficient. Otherwise, the call will fail within the try - catch.     3. The relay incentive is enough to get the message relayed within the expected time. If that is never, this check is not needed.

params.destinationAddress: The destination address encoded in 65 bytes: First byte is the length and last 64 is the destination address.
params.destinationIdentifier: 32 bytes which identifies the destination chain. The first 2 bytes are used for gas-saving context.
params.message: The message to be sent to the destination. Please ensure the message is block-unique.     This means that you don't send the same message twice in a single block.

returns.gasRefund: The amount of excess gas which was paid to this call. The app should handle the excess.
returns.messageIdentifier: An unique identifier for a message.

increaseBounty(bytes32,uint96,uint96).details: It is not possible to increase the gas budget for a message.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

processMessage(bytes,bytes,bytes32).details: This function is intended to be called by off-chain agents.  Please ensure that feeRecipitent can receive gas token: Either it is an EOA or a implement fallback() / receive().  Likewise for any non-evm chains. Otherwise the message fails (ack) or the relay payment is lost (call).  You need to pass in incentive.maxGas(Delivery|Ack) + messaging protocol dependent buffer, otherwise this call might fail.

params.feeRecipitent: An identifier for the the fee recipitent. The identifier should identify the relayer on the source chain.  For EVM (and this contract as a source), use the bytes32 encoded address. For other VMs you might have to register your address.
params.messagingProtocolContext: Additional context required to verify the message by the messaging protocol.
params.rawMessage: The raw message as it was emitted.

recoverAck(bytes,bytes).details: No applciation should rely on this function. It should only be used in-case an application has faulty logic.  Example: Faulty logic results in wrong enforcement on gas limit => out of gas?

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

MESSAGE_REVERTED().notice: If a swap reverts on the destination chain, 1 bytes is sent back instead. This is the byte.

NO_AUTHENTICATION().notice: If a swap reverts on the destination chain, 1 bytes is sent back instead. This is the byte.

SEND_LOST_GAS_TO().notice: If a relayer or application provides an address which cannot accept gas and the transfer fails the gas is sent here instead.

escrowMessage(bytes32,bytes,bytes,(uint4.notice: Set a bounty on a message and transfer the message to the messaging protocol.

increaseBounty(bytes32,uint96,uint96).notice: Increases the bounty for relaying messages

processMessage(bytes,bytes,bytes32).notice: Deliver a message which has been *signed* by a messaging protocol.

recoverAck(bytes,bytes).notice: Allows anyone to re-execute an ack which didn't properly execute.
